<h1>About Choco Explorer</h1>

<p><strong>Choco Explorer</strong> is a Ruby on Rails web application that collects and organizes real-world data about chocolate products using multiple sources.</p>

<h2>Data Sources</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>OpenFoodFacts API:</strong> This API provides chocolate data including product names, brands, categories, and countries of sale.</li>
  <li><strong>Faker Gem:</strong> This gem is used to generate realistic sample data such as customer reviews and brand descriptions.</li>
</ul>

<p>This site is built using the Rails 8 framework and is powered by Active Record models, associations, and validations. Data is seeded into the database and made available through intuitive navigation and search features.</p>
